<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Lesson: Prism & Pyramid Relationship</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Crimson+Pro:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Inter:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body { font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif; background: #fdfbf7; line-height: 1.7; }
        .page { background: white; max-width: 850px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 80px; box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); border-radius: 32px; border: 1px solid #f1f5f9; }
        .action { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 24px; color: #1e293b; font-size: 0.95rem; }
        .dialogue { margin-left: 40px; font-style: italic; color: #475569; position: relative; margin-bottom: 12px; }
        .dialogue::before { content: "-"; position: absolute; left: -20px; color: #cbd5e1; font-style: normal; }
        .material-box { background: #f8fafc; border-radius: 20px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; padding: 30px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
        .aside-box { background: #fffbeb; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; padding: 25px; margin: 40px 0; border-radius: 0 15px 15px 0; position: relative; }
        .aside-box::after { content: "Instructor's Aside"; position: absolute; top: -10px; left: 20px; background: #f59e0b; color: white; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 8px; font-weight: 900; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; }
        .illustrate { border: 2px dashed #e2e8f0; border-radius: 20px; margin: 35px 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: #fcfcfc; padding: 30px; }
        .formula { background: #F1F5F9; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; text-align: center; margin: 20px 0; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 800; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <article class="page">
        <header class="mb-12 border-b-2 border-amber-50 pb-8">
            <p class="font-sans font-bold text-amber-600 uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-2 italic">Geometry // Volume Narrative Step 10</p>
            <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 leading-tight">Prism & Pyramid Relationship</h1>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400 italic">Discovering the 1:3 Volume Ratio through Experiment</p>
        </header>

        <section class="material-box">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-bold text-[10px] uppercase text-slate-400 mb-4">Material Analysis</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 italic">Large hollow square-based rectangular prism, hollow square-based pyramid (same base/height), container of dry sand or soil, brush and dustpan.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-amber-600 mb-8 border-b pb-2 italic">Presentation</h2>

            <div class="action">Arrange the materials. Point out that the pyramid and prism have identical bases and heights.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">- "Do you think this pyramid holds as much sand as the prism? Let’s find out. I’m using soil today as a filler."</div>

            <div class="action">Pour three full pyramids into the prism. Observe it fills exactly to the top.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">- "It took exactly three pyramids. This means the volume of the pyramid is one-third the volume of the rectangular prism with the same base and height."</div>

            <div class="illustrate">
                <svg width="400" height="150" viewBox="0 0 400 150" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <!-- Pyramid pouring -->
                    <path d="M100 40 L60 120 L140 120 Z" stroke="#B45309" stroke-width="1.5" fill="#FDE68A" opacity="0.4"/>
                    <!-- Prism filling -->
                    <rect x="220" y="40" width="100" height="100" stroke="#94A3B8" stroke-width="2"/>
                    <rect x="220" y="106" width="100" height="34" fill="#FDE68A" opacity="0.4"/>
                    <!-- Stick figure -->
                    <g transform="translate(340, 90)">
                        <circle cx="10" cy="10" r="8" stroke="#CBD5E1" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                        <path d="M10 18 L10 40 M10 25 L-30 0" stroke="#CBD5E1" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                    </g>
                </svg>
                <div class="text-[10px] text-slate-400 mt-2 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest">FIG 10.1: POURING 1/3 RATIO</div>
            </div>

            <div class="formula">Volume (Pyramid) = (Base Area × Height) ÷ 3</div>

            <div class="aside-box text-sm italic text-amber-900 leading-relaxed">
                "I don’t recommend using flour or water—they are messy and can damage the wooden or metal solids. Soil or fine sand provides the most consistent sensorial result."
            </div>
        </section>

        <footer class="mt-20 pt-8 border-t text-[10px] font-sans text-slate-300 uppercase tracking-widest text-center">
            Elim Lee // Semester 4 Sprint // AMI Elementary
        </footer>
    </article>
</body>
</html>
